          <zone h='15125' id='9' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='9875'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Across all U.S. climate zones, the relative ranking of PUE sensitivity drivers is remarkably consistent. UPS efficiency overwhelmingly dominates variance in PUE, followed by airflow pressure, power distribution losses, and air-side temperature control. While the magnitude of secondary sensitivities varies modestly by climate, the hierarchy of influential parameters remains stable. This indicates that climate primarily affects the frequency of operational stress conditions rather than redefining which control levers govern efficiency.</run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
